# extio-zephyr app-level Kconfig overrides.
# Sourced by the Zephyr build before the upstream defaults, so a `default` here
# wins for promptless symbols.

# DO NOT override USBD_CDC_ACM_TX_DELAY_MS (upstream default 100 ms).
#
# It looks like a Linux-tty quirk, so this app briefly set it to 0. That caused
# every console symptom we chased for a day: shredded output, mangled ANSI
# escapes, and terminals dropping mid-command on BOTH macOS and Linux.
#
# The delay is protection, not a workaround. A host tty starts with ECHO ON and
# the opening application disables it a moment later; the delay keeps the device
# quiet through that window. Transmit into it and the host reflects the banner
# and prompt straight back into our RX -- the shell then reads its own output as
# input, answers it, and that answer gets echoed back again. A feedback storm.
#
# The frame-pipe CDC survived it because its framer resyncs on '>' and silently
# discards junk. The console is the only endpoint that REPLIES, so it is the only
# one that amplifies. If an interactive console ever misbehaves again, check this
# symbol before suspecting the terminal or the host OS.

source "Kconfig.zephyr"
